==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κριτικός]]''' (''kritikos'') "of or for judging, able to discern" < '''[[κρίσις]]''' "''[[crisis]]''"

===Noun===
'''critic''' (''plural:'' [[critics]])
# a person who appraises on the works of others
# a specialist in judging works of art
# one who criticizes; a person who finds fault
# an opponent

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[arvostelija]] (1,3), [[kriitikko]] (1,2)
*French: [[critique]] ''m'' (1-3), [[détracteur]]/-trice ''m/f'' (4)
*Greek: [[κριτικός]] (''kritikos'') ''m''
*Telugu: [[విమర్శకుడు]] (vimarSakuDu) ''m'', [[విమర్శకురాలు]] (vimarSakuraalu) ''f''

